methods.void clear(): Removes all of the mappings from this map.
methods.Object clone(): Returns a shallow copy of this identity hash map: the keys and values themselves are not cloned.
methods.boolean containsKey(Object key): Tests whether the specified object reference is a key in this identity hash map.
methods.boolean containsValue(Object value): Tests whether the specified object reference is a value in this identity hash map.
methods.Set entrySet(): Returns a Set view of the mappings contained in this map.
methods.boolean equals(Object o): Compares the specified object with this map for equality.
methods.void forEach(BiConsumer action): Performs the given action for each entry in this map until all entries have been processed or the action throws an exception.
methods.V get(Object key): Returns the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if this map contains no mapping for the key.
methods.int hashCode(): Returns the hash code value for this map.
methods.boolean isEmpty(): Returns true if this identity hash map contains no key-value mappings.
methods.Set keySet(): Returns an identity-based set view of the keys contained in this map.
methods.V put(K key, V value): Associates the specified value with the specified key in this identity hash map.
methods.void putAll(Map m): Copies all of the mappings from the specified map to this map.
methods.V remove(Object key): Removes the mapping for this key from this map if present.
methods.void replaceAll(BiFunction function): Replaces each entry's value with the result of invoking the given function on that entry until all entries have been processed or the function throws an exception.
methods.int size(): Returns the number of key-value mappings in this identity hash map.
methods.Collection values(): Returns a Collection view of the values contained in this map.
